Morty is split up into billions of different NPCs.

498
00:22:41.000 --> 00:22:43.000
What about me? Am I your grandson?

499
00:22:43.000 --> 00:22:45.000
I just said everyone is.

500
00:22:45.000 --> 00:22:46.000
Wow.

501
00:22:46.000 --> 00:22:48.000
I got really excited about that idea,

502
00:22:48.000 --> 00:22:54.000
because it's simultaneously an almost possible-to-grasp kind of simulation theory,

503
00:22:54.000 --> 00:23:00.000
while simultaneously being a really perfect model for almost any organized religion.

504
00:23:00.000 --> 00:23:02.000
Your family had a perfectly fine religion.

505
00:23:02.000 --> 00:23:03.000
You erased Jewish.

506
00:23:03.000 --> 00:23:11.000
They all come back around to this idea that we don't have to worry about whatever we think

507
00:23:11.000 --> 00:23:14.000
our little tiny scripted jam is,

508
00:23:14.000 --> 00:23:18.000
because we're all part of some larger thing with a bigger destiny.

509
00:23:18.000 --> 00:23:21.000
And the way that intersects with simulation theory, of course,

510
00:23:21.000 --> 00:23:26.000
is that bigger destiny might be that you're a 14-year-old kid whose toast is burning.

511
00:23:26.000 --> 00:23:31.000
You may be rushing to a tone with an impersonal cosmos for no reason.

512
00:23:31.000 --> 00:23:39.000
You may have a better gig as an unenlightened tripe in someone else's fractured amusement.

